        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Center Post, or 9 miles
northwest of Summerville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, dime sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, La Fayette, Center Post, and Linwood.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
